 not revolutionaries and do not reject national identity, but they do question the equation of state and nation. Herzfeld explores the political strengths and vulnerabilities of their deployment of heritage and the weaknesses they expose in the bureaucratic and ethnonational state in an era of accelerated globalization.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aAuthorityxSocial aspects. 0aMarginality, SocialxPolitical aspects. 0aNation-state. 0aNational characteristicsxPolitical aspects. 0aNationalismxSocial aspects. 0aPolitical crimes and offenseszGreecezCrete. 0aPolitical crimes and offenseszThailandzBangkok. 0aState crimes. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh1 aFoster, Robert J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReichman, Daniel R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311074331908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021 Englishz978311075418608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021z9783110753967oZDB-23-DSL40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478022244?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478022244423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478022244/original  a978-3-11-074331-9  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075418-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021 Englishb2021  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA